{
  "texts": [
    "For this part, we collected about 10,000 training examples, where the labels (hallucinated vs. not hallucinated) are produced by GPT-4 detection, and the features are entities and their confidence scores from the NER, confidence score from NLI, and the confidence score from SBD.",
    "We adopt the Gradient Boosting Decision Tree to leverage the diverse AI feedback and fine-tune a model using scikit-learn to generate a single numerical value indicating the confidence or likelihood that the text to be checked (i.e., response, summary, or single sentence) is hallucinated.",
    "With AI feedback from different sources, we formulated prompts based on a pre-defined template to guide GPT-4 in correcting hallucinations.",
    "We explored two distinct rewriting prompts:",
    "Rewriting prompt v1."
  ]
}